<br>
At some point someone claimed useing larger than .50 caliber weapons against personel violated this standard.  It was quickly dismissed and had not been adopted as a standard by ANY of the Contracting Parties.<br>
<br>
A similar myth developed about Airborne trooops.  Some believe that the GC outlaws shooting Combat troops while they are decsending in parachutes.  This is noit true the prohipition against targeting parachutes was ONLY to apply to those escapeing damaged aircraft (qualifying as non-combatants.)  Airborne troops are combatants, mid-drop or not and so are legal targets, even in mid-air.<br>
