I read and understand that, but there is a disconnect going on between what is written above and how the GC is being implemented in world politics/law.  What that is telling me is that we are all missing something.<br>
<br>
Why is it refered to as the &quot;Geneva Convention&quot;, when there are really four Conventions, and two Protocols?  I've seen it refered to as both Geneva Convention and Conventions.  Is there a difference?<br>
